Manchester City boss, Pep Guardiola, has singled out Tottenham Hotspur striker Harry Kane for praise following his side’s Premier League 1-0 defeat against Spurs on Sunday. Guardiola watched as Tottenham defeated Man City in an away Premier League tie following Kane’s only goal of the match. Speaking at his post-match press conference, Guardiola said, “I am not going to say the Harry Kane team otherwise, Poch will be grumpy with me and I don’t want it. “On behalf of Man City, I can say congrats on this incredible milestone. He is an exceptional player. The result against Tottenham means Man City are five points behind leaders Arsenal on the log.